      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on the bottom of tomato plants can be a sign of a few different issues, but one common cause is a lack of light, especially if the plant is growing in a shaded area. You might need to provide more sunlight for your tomatoes, or consider pruning the lower leaves to allow more light to reach the fruiting branches. It's also possible that the plant is experiencing nutrient deficiencies, such as nitrogen or iron, which can cause yellowing leaves. Check the soil pH and nutrient levels to determine if that's the issue. \n\nYou can also try repotting the plant in a well-draining potting mix and fertilizing with a balanced fertilizer. If the problem persists, consider getting a soil test to determine if there are any underlying issues.",
